
[1]hoe

   HOE, n. ho. A farmer's instrument for cutting up weeds and loosening
   the earth in fields and gardens. It is in shape something like an adz,
   being a plate of iron, with an eye for a handle, which is set at an
   acute angle with the plate.

   HOE, v.t. To cut,dig, scrape or clean with a hoe; as, to hoe the earth
   in a garden; to hoe the beds.

   1. To clear from weeds; as, to hoe maiz; to hoe cabbages.

                           HOE, v.i. To use a hoe.
